				\begin{document}$$\ell (a ,b)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M82"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>ℓ</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>a</mml:mi><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>b</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4079_Article_IEq34.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the negative log-likelihood for an observation e.g. for the linear Gaussian case it is <inline-formula id="IEq35"><alternatives><tex-math id="M83">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
