        <p id="Par45">It is revealed that using the screening step to reduce the irrelevant covariates not only reduces the dimension of the data, but can also improve the heritability estimation, in particular for the scenario of removing 60% of the covariates. This fact has also been reported before in the linear mixed model approach in [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR27">27</xref>], where the authors show an improvement of the maximum likelihood estimation. However, if too many covariates are removed, heritability estimation can be inaccurate as in the scenario of keeping only top <inline-formula id="IEq65"><alternatives><tex-math id="M145">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
